@{b}Acknowledgements@{ub}

Switch was inspired by Multi-Con by Chris Swift; a metric conversion
utility written in AMOS.  Switch isn't based on Chris's code.

Thanks must go to the following band of beta-testers:
    Dave Hardenbrook
    Dave Manley
    Gernod Schomberg
    Chris Underwood
    Glen Watts

Without the help of these people, Switch would be full of bugs.

Gernod Schomberg gets an extra thankyou for translating this guide
into German.  I would also like to thank Johan Alfredsson and Henrik
Nilsson for providing the Swedish translation of this document.
Thanks, guys :-)


Next section: @{"History" link "History"}

@endnode


@node "History" "Switch 1.2 Program History"
@next "Legal"
@prev "Acknowledgements"
Previous section: @{"Acknowledgements" link "Acknowledgements" 0}


@{b}Program History@{ub}

- Version 0.1 (25-Aug-96, beta release)
Ę First version.

- Version 0.11 (30-Aug-96, beta release)
Ę Small bug in code to disable input gadget fixed.
Ę Name of conversion between litres and gallons changed to "Litres <->
  Brit. Gallons" (unambiguous).
Ę Added "Litres <-> US Gallons" conversion.
Ę Gadget labels changed from black to white.

- Version 1.0▀1 (9-Oct-96, beta release)
Ę Code cleanup, no change in functionality.
Ę Version numbering changed to be more Amiga-standard.

- Version 1.0▀2 (30-Oct-96, beta release)
Ę Menus as well as gadgets are now disabled when the "about" window
  is active.

- Version 1.0 (11-Dec-96, first public release)
Ę Public release of 1.0▀2.
Ę Switch now centres its window on any width of Workbench screen.

- Version 1.1▀1 (24-Mar-97, beta release)
Ę Switch now attempts to adapt to the screen font (within reason).
Ę "TOPAZ" and "AUTOACTIVATE" tooltypes added.
Ę "Shrink" button added to window title bar.
Ę Abbreviations removed, eg "Fht." is now written "Fahrenheit".
Ę The "About..." requester is now asynchronous.

- Version 1.1▀2 (21-Apr-97, beta release)
Ę Bug fix: the About requester now responds to the LAMIGA-V and LAMIGA-B
  keyboard shortcuts.
Ę If run from the Shell, Switch will now quit if the Shell process
  is sent a Ctrl-C.
Ę Many optimizations have been carried out, mostly involving copious
  amounts of assembly language.  The result is a smaller, more efficient
  binary.

- Version 1.1 (7-Jul-97, public release)
Ę Public release of 1.1▀2.
Ę Bug fix: the code to test whether Switch had successfully opened a
  window was unreliable.  It was a really stupid bug as well.  I
  deserve a slap round the face with a stack pointer.

- Version 1.2▀1 (21-Jul-97, beta release)
Ę Scrollback system added.
Ę Print feature added.
Ę Code reorganized and optimized (again).
Ę The "About" requester is now synchronous again :-)

- Version 1.2 (31-Dec-97, public release)
Ę Public release of 1.2▀1.
Ę Printing improved; sixty-second timeout added.
Ę Switch now defaults to the scrollback window open; the tooltype
  SCROLLBACK has been changed for NOSCROLLBACK.


Next section: @{"Legal Matters" link "Legal" 0}

